    slug: "rijaal-al-quran-7-volume-set",
    description: `Rijaal-al-Quran (7 Volume Set) is an encyclopedic Arabic-language work that provides comprehensive biographical entries for every individual named in the Holy Quran, representing one of the most ambitious and thorough scholarly projects in the field of Quranic studies. The title translates to "The Men of the Quran" or "The Personalities of the Quran," and this seven-volume set systematically covers the prophets, messengers, companions of prophets, righteous individuals, opponents of the prophets, and other notable figures who are mentioned by name in the Quranic text. Each biographical entry draws upon the Quranic verses that mention the individual, the authentic hadith and reports from the Prophetic tradition, the classical works of Quranic exegesis (tafsir), the major historical sources, and the biographical dictionaries of the Islamic scholarly tradition to construct a comprehensive portrait of each figure.

The seven volumes of this work are organized to cover the full range of personalities mentioned in the Quran. The early volumes focus on the major prophets and messengers whose stories are narrated in detail in the Quran, including Adam, Nuh (Noah), Ibrahim (Abraham), Musa (Moses), Isa (Jesus), and Muhammad (peace be upon them all). For each prophet, the book provides a detailed discussion of the Quranic narrative, the historical context of their mission, the key lessons and guidance that can be derived from their story, and the scholarly discussions surrounding various aspects of their lives. Subsequent volumes cover the other prophets who are mentioned more briefly in the Quran, the righteous companions and supporters of the prophets, the angels and jinn who interact with humans in the Quranic narrative, and the opponents and enemies of the prophets whose stories serve as warnings and lessons. Each entry includes a thorough analysis of every Quranic verse in which the person is mentioned, the various scholarly opinions regarding ambiguous aspects of their stories, and the practical lessons that contemporary Muslims can derive from their examples.

The scholarly methodology of this work is particularly noteworthy. The author has undertaken an exhaustive survey of the major tafsir works, including those of Ibn Kathir, at-Tabari, al-Qurtubi, as-Sa'di, and other classical and contemporary commentators, to compile the most comprehensive and balanced understanding of each personality. Where scholars differ in their interpretation of a Quranic passage, the author presents the different views with their supporting evidence, allowing the reader to understand the range of scholarly opinion on each topic. The Arabic text is printed in clear typography with generous margins, and each volume includes comprehensive indexes that allow readers to locate specific personalities, Quranic verses, and topics. This seven-volume set is an essential reference for scholars of Quranic studies, students of Islamic theology and history, imams and religious educators, and institutional libraries that serve the needs of advanced Islamic studies programs.`,
    metaDescription: "Rijaal-al-Quran 7 Volume Set: Arabic encyclopedia of every personality named in the Quran. Prophets, companions, and opponents with tafsir analysis."
